1- clautolisp must support all the encoding supported by its underlying CL implementation,
   and this must include at minima US-ASCII, ISO-8859-1, WINDOWS-1252 and UTF-8.
   (use babel).
   
2- processing of -e and -E options. When they're not given, they must
take as default encoding what is specified by the environment
variables: LC_ALL or else LANG or else LC_CTYPE. And by default, if no
-e -E and no environment variable, US-ASCII.

So *AUTOLISP-FILE-ENCODING* and *AUTOLISP-TERMINAL-ENCODING* can never be NIL.


